org.hibernate.sql.results.spi

Interface SqlSelectionReader<T>

  • Deprecated. 
    Use JdbcValueExtractor instead

    @Deprecated
public interface SqlSelectionReader<T>
    A low-level reader for extracting JDBC results. We always extract "basic" values via this contract; various other contracts may consume those basic vales into compositions like an entity, embeddable or collection. SqlSelectionReader generally "wraps" a org.hibernate.type.descriptor.spi.ValueExtractor and dispatches its calls to that wrapped ValueExtractor. The SqlSelectionReader result is generally used to populate the "current row JDBC values" array (RowProcessingState.getJdbcValue(org.hibernate.sql.results.spi.SqlSelection))
